<title>[@@@@@@@@@]</title>

<statement>
  <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li><p>3:32 p.m. Sample responses:</p><ul>
<li>From 2:45, it is 15 minutes from 2:45 to 3:00 and another 30 minutes to 3:30. That's 45 minutes, so 47 minutes from 2:45 would be 3:32.</li>
<li>I know that 60 minutes from 2:45 is 3:45, and 47 minutes is 13 minutes before 3:45, which is 3:32 p.m.</li>
</ul>
      </li>
      <li><p>No. Sample response:</p><ul>
<li>I know that 4:40 is 30 minutes from 5:10 p.m. If the show is shorter than 30 minutes, it must have started after 4:40.</li>
<li>I know that 20 minutes before 5:10 is 4:50, so 24 minutes before 5:10 is 4:46, which is after 4:40.</li>
</ul>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


